# Gmail MCP Server Environment Configuration
# This file documents the configuration options for the Gmail MCP Server

# ==============================================================================
# CREDENTIAL PATHS
# ==============================================================================
# By default, the Gmail MCP server uses fixed paths for credentials:
# - Credentials: ~/.gmail-mcp-credentials.json
# - Token: ~/.gmail-mcp-token.json
#
# These paths are hardcoded in src/index.ts (lines 24-25).
# To use custom paths, you would need to modify the source code or set
# environment variables if supported in future versions.

# Optional: If you want to use environment variables for paths (requires code modification)
# GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/your/credentials.json
# GMAIL_TOKEN_PATH=/path/to/your/token.json

# ==============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==============================================================================
# 1. Download your OAuth 2.0 credentials from Google Cloud Console
# 2. Save as ~/.gmail-mcp-credentials.json
# 3. Run: npm run auth
# 4. Follow the authentication prompts
# 5. Token will be saved to ~/.gmail-mcp-token.json

# ==============================================================================
# REQUIRED GOOGLE CLOUD SCOPES
# ==============================================================================
# When setting up your OAuth consent screen, ensure these scopes are added:
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.send
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify

# ==============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================================================
# - Never commit credentials.json or token.json files to version control
# - Keep your OAuth client secret secure
# - Regularly review authorized applications in your Google account
# - Consider using separate Google accounts for testing vs production
